definition.value: An alkane that is pentane substituted by a methyl group at positions 2 and 3.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-D-galactosamine residues all linked sequentially (1->3).
An organic heterobicylic compound that is piperazine with an ethane-1,2-diyl group forming a bridge between N1 and N4. It is typically used as a catalyst in polymerization reactions.
